This world configuration creates islands using the following steps: 1: Set land rarity to 100 to prevent oceans from spawning. 2: Create a custom sea biome that counts as a normal biome, not as an ocean (creating custom biomes can be done via the "Manage worlds menu", don't forget to add your biome to CustomBiomes in the world settings). 3: Create islands, each kind of island has a "foundation" biome, these are basic biome types like plains or swamp. All the foundation biomes have NotBorderNear configured so that they can only border a sea or beach biome, this makes sure that all islands are seperated by sea and can have beaches as border biomes. Only foundation biomes and the sea biome are added to the NormalBiomes list in the World settings so only those will spawn normally, other biomes will be spawned inside the foundation biomes using IsleInBiome. 4: For each foundation biome configure any kind of beach biome as the BorderBiome. 5: In order to add valleys and hills etc to the island interiors configure biomes (such as Plains M and Swamp M) as IsleInBiome biomes for any foundation biome and edit their BiomeHeight and BiomeVolatility. Along with some completely customised islands this world configuration has 2 basic island shapes, flat and mountainous, that are used for several islands. You can make many more island shapes and completely customised islands!
